      <h1 class="blog-title">What Is Legacy Odyssey?</h1>

      <p class="blog-meta">Overview &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; 4 min read</p>

      <div class="blog-body">

        <p>Legacy Odyssey is a digital baby book — built as a real website at your child's own .com domain. Your baby gets their name as a website. Parents fill in milestones, photos, and letters through the iOS &amp; Android app. Family visits the book at your-childs-name.com, straight from any browser. Password-protected.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>It's a website, not an app</h2>

        <p>Most platforms keep your content locked inside an app. Your family has to download it, create an account, and get added before they see anything.</p>

        <p>Legacy Odyssey works differently. Every customer gets an actual .com domain — registered in your child's name at checkout. Grandma opens it in Safari on her iPad. Dad's coworkers can look at it from a work computer. No app. No signup. Just a URL and a password.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Two ways to edit</h2>

        <p>You can build your book from the <strong>iOS or Android app</strong>, or from the <strong>web editor</strong> at legacyodyssey.com/account. Both give you access to every section. Changes sync immediately.</p>

        <p>Sections include:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Welcome / Child Info — the opening page, birth stats, hero photo</li>
          <li>Before You Arrived — the pregnancy, in cards</li>
          <li>Birth Story — two perspectives written separately</li>
          <li>Your Journey to Us — for adoption, surrogacy, or any non-traditional path</li>
          <li>Coming Home — the first days, in cards</li>
          <li>Month by Month — months 1–12, each with a photo and note</li>
          <li>Our Family — portraits, bios, and albums for everyone in your child's life</li>
          <li>Your Firsts — a running milestone list</li>
          <li>Celebrations — birthdays and holidays, by year, with galleries <em>(paid)</em></li>
          <li>Letters to You — letters from family members, displayed as letter-style cards <em>(paid)</em></li>
          <li>Family Recipes — full recipe format with ingredients, steps, and galleries <em>(paid)</em></li>
          <li>Their Keepsakes — clothing, toys, and mementos with photos <em>(paid)</em></li>
          <li>The Vault — sealed items for your child to open later <em>(paid)</em></li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <h2>What family sees</h2>

        <p>Every section you fill in becomes a page on the website. The site has a consistent design throughout — warm cream background, gold accents, left-side navigation. It reads like a printed book, not a social media feed.</p>

        <hr>

        <p><a href="https://legacyodyssey.com">Get started at legacyodyssey.com</a></p>

